HEADWORD: Canonry
<hw>Can"on*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <er>Canonries</er>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>. <def>A benefice or prebend in a cathedral or collegiate
church; a right to a place in chapter and to a portion of its revenues;
the dignity or emoluments of a canon.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

